  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat your oven to 200°C."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Take the top off the peppers, remove the stem and chop into 2cm cubes. Peel and cut each red onion into 8 wedges. Add them onto a baking tray with 2 tbsp of olive oil, season with salt and pepper. Roast the veggies for 25-30 mins until softened and starting to char in places."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, add the giant couscous to a sieve and give it a rinse. Cook the giant couscous per package instructions, then drain and wash under cold water until cold to the touch."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "While the couscous cooks, drain the chickpeas and transfer to a bowl. Chop the tomatoes into 1cm cubes and add to the bowl. Zest 1 of the lemons and add to the bowl, finely chop the parsley leaves and stalks and add them as well."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To make the tahini dressing, add the tahini and the juice of both lemons. Whisk in water, 1 tbsp of water at a time, to loosen. Season with salt, pepper and sugar (if needed). Tip into the chickpea bowl along with the drained giant couscous. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once the veggies are roasted, toss them through the couscous and chickpea salad along with the watercress."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Share into plates or spoon onto a platter and finish with a scattering of feta and flaked almonds."
    }
  ],
